data.sampled: The strategy being implemented is a diagonal call spread. The options are being used to control the risk by selling the expensive call option and buying the cheaper put option. The main goal is to achieve a profit when the underlying asset is close to or at the specified strike prices.

prompt.content: Assume all contracts are for 100 shares. Answer with no explanation, only a classification. Given the expiration dates are the same, what is the name of the option strategy being implemented in the following? Sell 1 $42 strike price put at $1.28. Buy 1 $40 strike price put at $0.85. Sell 1 $47 strike price call at $0.86. Buy 1 $48 strike price call at $0.57.
